title: For Sale:  Custom AR-15, PWS Piston Rifle
postcontent:
The best of both worlds between the AK and AR systems.
This rifle was my dream build, but due to budget constraints, I have to sell her. The heart of the build is the PWS upper, with the long-stroke (AK47-style) piston system. The upper less than a year old, but is no longer in production. Consider this upper to be better than the current production, because the bolt carrier and piston are nickel teflon coated and the current production PWS uppers are not. This upper also has one more gas block position than the current production does (2 positions for standard shooting, 2 positions for suppressed shooting). She's had less than 100 rounds through her, just enough to properly break in the barrel. Great rifle, super easy to clean, and PWS is known for their reliability. 
Tech specs and parts:
PWS MK116 upper with a 4 position gas block, melonited 1:8 twist barrel, chambered in .223 Wylde (5.56 and .223), PWS flash hider/ muzzle brake, keymod rail with 2 moveable picatinny rail sections
POF anti-tilt buffer tube
Magpul stock and grip
CMMG Lower parts kit 
Hand-polished trigger parts
Single-point sling end plate
Large winter trigger guard
KAK H2 buffer and buffer spring
30 round USGI mag
Also included is a gas block instruction guide, gas block adjustment and removal tool/ front sight adjustment tool
 
Just because I know I'm going to get low-ball offers, I have to state this. THIS IS NOT THE CHEAP CURRENT PRODUCTION PWS UPPER. This is the original Mod 1 series. The MSRP for the upper alone was $1450 before PWS discontinued this model for their cheaper Mod 1-P upper. This rifle is seriously priced to sell. My loss, your gain. 
Thanks for looking.

postcontent: The Combat Carry was a very limited production run from the Kimber Custom Shop and was a Series 1 weapon. From what I can find online, there were fewer than 1000 of these guns produced in the late 90s. I've also read that some folks in the Kimber Custom Shop say the Combat Carry is the best gun they ever produced. I don't know if that is just hyperbole or actual statements, but I can say I've shot a lot of guns, and this is a great gun. Mine is the only one in the country for sale on Armslist right now. This is an amazingly accurate smaller 1911 and is one of my favorite guns to shoot. But I don't have a real use for it now; so it is (regretfully) up for sale.A prior owner paid over $300 to have it professional Cerakoted in tri-tone (black frame, gray trigger and safety, silver/chrome slide), and it is really gorgeous. Unfortunately, the Cerakoting undercuts the collectibility of the gun. However, it's still a very rare, premium gun and is in terrific condition. On the range, it runs like a champ. It is very consistent and accurate and is a real joy to shoot. The size, and the nice Carekoting, make it work very well for carry, too.Includes: + Original Kimber clamshell box.+ One 7-round Wilson Combat stainless magazine.+ One generic 8-round stainless magazine. It does *not* include paperwork or original factory magazines. This is not a collectible; it's a premium, rare model handgun in excellent condition.Specs:+ Compact 4" barrel.+ Officer size alloy frame.+ Weight 28 oz, empty.+ Match-grade aluminum trigger.+ Kimber Meprolight Night Sights (a little dim, but still work).+ Right-hand safety.+ 30 LPI checkered front strap.+ All edges are rounded/melted to reduce drag.I'm not wild about selling this gun, but I've added a few to the collection recently, and my wife tells me some guns have to go. Please also see my other listings.Asking $800 OBO. LOCAL SALES ONLY. MUST BE ABLE TO MEET FACE TO FACE IN THE TRIANGLE. Cash or certified funds only. Prefer to sell, although I will consider a few specific guns for trade.
